import React, { useEffect, useState } from "react"; import { useParams } from "react-router-dom"; import axiosInstance from "../../baseurl"; import axios from "axios"; function ViewPrograms() { const { id } = useParams(); const [tutorialdata, settutdata] = useState({ title:"", category:"", video:null, pgmid:id, trainerid:localStorage.getItem('Trainerlogid'), description:"", chapterNo:"" }) const [viewprogrambyid, setprogrambyid] = useState({}) useEffect(()=>{ axiosInstance.post(`/viewPgmById/${id}`) .then((res)=>{ console.log(res, 'view prograrm by id'); setprogrambyid(res.data.data) }) .catch((err)=>{ console.log(err); }) axiosInstance.post(`/viewtutorialByPgmId/${id}`) .then((res)=>{console.log(res);}) .catch((err)=>{console.log(err);}) },[]) const changefn = (e)=>{ if(e.target.name=='video'){ settutdata({...tutorialdata, video:e.target.files[0]}) } else{ settutdata({...tutorialdata, [e.target.name]:e.target.value}) } } const subfn = (e)=>{ e.preventDefault() axiosInstance.post(`/addtutorial`, tutorialdata, { headers: { 'Content-Type': 'multipart/form-data', }}) .then((res) => { console.log(res); }) .catch((err) => { console.log(err); }); } return

{viewprogrambyid.title}
